      version="1.2.1.qualifier"
      provider-name="CentraleSupélec/LRI">

   <description url="http://wwwdi.supelec.fr/software/TESL/">
      The Tagged Event Specification Language allows the specification of timed systems by modeling events as clocks and occurrences of an event as ticks on its clock.
Both event-triggered and time-triggered models are supported through the use of implication relations between clocks and of relations between the time scale of the clocks.
   </description>

